.TH "expand_dfs_referral" 9 "expand_dfs_referral" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
expand_dfs_referral \- Perform a dfs referral query and update the cifs_sb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" expand_dfs_referral
.BI "(const unsigned int xid "  ","
.BI "struct cifs_ses *ses "  ","
.BI "struct smb3_fs_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct cifs_sb_info *cifs_sb "  ","
.BI "char *ref_path "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xid" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "ses" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "ctx" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "cifs_sb" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "ref_path" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

If a referral is found, cifs_sb->ctx->mount_options will be (re-)allocated
to a string containing updated options for the submount.  Otherwise it
will be left untouched.

Returns the rc from get_dfs_path to the caller, which can be used to
determine whether there were referrals.
